{"id":14881360,"mediaExerciseId":"e8c29552-f61d-4996-9d9b-e7dd23a3f6ec","exerciseName":"14","chapterName":"12","chapterTitle":"Some Lessons From Capital Market History","groupId":612363,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":417,"solutions":[{"id":6232121,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to solve for the missing data using the concept of averages. Moreover, we need to solve for the standard deviation using the given data. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We know that in order to get the average return, we will add all the returns and divide it by the total number of years. This will give us the formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{average return}&=\\dfrac{\\text{Sum of all values for return}}{\\text{number of years}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"For this, we will use x as the variable for the missing value. Substituting the known values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n10.8&=\\dfrac{9-16+18+14+x}{5}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Cross-multiply and you will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n54&=9-16+18+14+x\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Isolate the variable to get the value for x:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nx&=38\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThis means that the value for the missing return is $38\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"To solve for the standard deviation, we will use this formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\sqrt{\\sigma^2}&=\\sqrt{\\dfrac{\\sum(x-\\text{mean})^2}{n-1}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere x is the value for the return and n is the number of years.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"Substituting the values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\sqrt{\\sigma^2}&=\\sqrt{\\dfrac{(9-10.8)^2+(-16-10.8)^2+(18-10.8)^2+(14-10.8)^2+(38-10.8)^2}{5-1}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"Simplify the equation to get the standard deviation:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\sqrt{\\sigma^2}&=\\sqrt{\\dfrac{1523.4}{4}}\\\\[15 pt]\n\\sigma&=\\sqrt{380.85}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=19.52\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe standard deviation for this set of data is $19.52$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3055d066-1ffc-4478-bba9-231fb79b42be","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":8}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881361,"exerciseName":"15","page":417,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"376ed077-7b48-425a-aeb1-f4ef0b9ef866","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-15-376ed077-7b48-425a-aeb1-f4ef0b9ef866"},{"id":14881362,"exerciseName":"16","page":417,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"99434ecb-17f5-4a99-8528-00136e415e12","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-16-99434ecb-17f5-4a99-8528-00136e415e12"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881359,"exerciseName":"13","page":416,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7084a16b-0220-41f3-a1ad-6807fab9465a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-13-7084a16b-0220-41f3-a1ad-6807fab9465a"},{"id":14881358,"exerciseName":"12","page":416,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ba6ae3e3-6039-445b-89e2-8f5c2586c958","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-12-ba6ae3e3-6039-445b-89e2-8f5c2586c958"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-14-e8c29552-f61d-4996-9d9b-e7dd23a3f6ec"}